Sphincteractis sanmatiensis Zamponi 1976
; Riemann-Zürneck 1986 ; Zamponi & Acuña 1992 ; Acuña & Zamponi 1995 ; Excoffon & Acuña 1995 ; Genzano et al. 1996;
Zamponi et al. 1998
a;
Zamponi et al. 1998
b; Häussermann & Försterra 2005; Fautin et al. 2007;
Rodríguez et al. 2007
; Lauretta et al. 2009; Häussermann 2010; Fautin 2016 .

Internal anatomy.
Longitudinal muscles of tentacles and oral disc ectodermal (
Fig. 3a,b,d
). Pharynx about 1/5 (rarely 1/2) of column length (preserved). Mesogloea thicker than other layers (to 
110 µm
at pharynx level), thicker in distal column than in proximal column, pedal and oral disc. Up to 64 mesenteries in 3 cycles (8+8+16=32 pairs), last cycle imperfect. Many irregularities found. Same number of mesenteries in proximal and distal part of column. All oldest mesenteries and some younger fertile. One siphonoglyph attached to a pair of directives. Retractor muscles diffuse, weak (
Fig. 3f
). No basilar nor parietobasilar muscles (
Fig. 3e
). Sphincter endodermal, diffuse, weak but clearly visible (
Fig. 3a,c
).
